===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|knitten|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang}} {{term|cnyttan||to fasten, tie, bind, knit; add, append|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|knutjanan|lang=gem-pro}}, {{recons|knuttijanan||to make knots, knit|lang=gem-pro}}. Cognate with Old Norse {{term|knýta|lang=non}} (Danish {{term|knytte|lang=da}}) and Northern German {{term|knütten|lang=de}}. More at {{l|en|knot}}.

